Live GB BESS Benchmark — static site
=====================================

This folder is a self-contained static site (plain HTML/CSS/JS, Plotly.js via
CDN) that visualises the live GB BESS benchmark artifacts written under
`docs/data/` by the live pipeline.

Layout
------
  index.html   Shell + navigation (Latest, History, Day-types, Methodology).
  styles.css   Styling.
  app.js       Data loader, Plotly figure renderer, view routing.
  .nojekyll    Tells GitHub Pages to serve files/dirs starting with `_`
               (e.g. `data/figs/_history/`) verbatim, bypassing Jekyll.
  data/        JSON artifacts (manifest.json, latest.json, history.json,
               days/<date>.json, figs/<date>/*.json). A small committed
               fixture is checked in so the page has something to show before
               the first live Action run commits real data.

Running locally
---------------
From this `docs/` directory:

    python -m http.server 8000

then open http://localhost:8000/ . All data paths are relative, so the site
also works when served from a GitHub Pages project subpath.

Enabling GitHub Pages
---------------------
In the repository on GitHub:

  1. Settings -> Pages.
  2. Under "Build and deployment", set Source to "Deploy from a branch".
  3. Choose the branch you publish from and the `/docs` folder, then Save.
  4. After the Pages build finishes, the site is served at
     https://<owner>.github.io/<repo>/ .

The `.nojekyll` file in this folder must remain committed so Pages serves the
`data/figs/_history/` artifacts correctly.
